---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Ship Captains | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Ship Captains working internationally, covering maritime command positions abroad, shipping careers, and global maritime opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Ship Captains";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Ship Captains working abroad, commanding vessels internationally, and pursuing careers across maritime operations worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/ship-captain-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/ship-captain-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Ship Captain Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Ship Captains command vessels, bearing ultimate responsibility for ship safety, crew, cargo, and operations. International maritime careers offer opportunities to navigate global waters, work with multinational crews, and experience shipping across international trade routes.
      </p>
      <p>
        International captain positions exist through shipping companies, cruise lines, offshore operators, and specialized maritime services worldwide.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Ship Captains working abroad across maritime operations worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Ship Captains</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually employer-provided' },
          { need: 'Maritime medical', why: 'Medical certificate requirements', typical: 'Essential for role' },
          { need: 'Emergency evacuation', why: 'Remote ocean locations', typical: 'Critical for role' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'Command isolation and stress', typical: 'Important for role' },
          { need: 'Loss of license', why: 'Medical decertification risk', typical: 'Essential for captains' },
          { need: 'Telemedicine', why: 'Limited shore access', typical: 'Often included' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Command Isolation</h3>
      <p>
        Ship captains bear ultimate responsibility for vessel operations, often in isolation at sea. Command decisions affect crew safety and cargo worth millions. The psychological burden of constant responsibility creates unique mental health demands. Extended time away from family compounds these challenges.
      </p>
      <p>
        Mental health support and telemedicine access help manage the isolation inherent in maritime command.
      </p>

      <h3>Remote Location Medical</h3>
      <p>
        Ships operate far from medical facilities for extended periods. Emergency medical situations require evacuation capabilities. Maritime medical requirements parallel aviation in stringency. Loss of medical certification means loss of command authority.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Container Shipping</h3>
      <p>
        Major shipping line. Company benefits. Global routes. Container shipping offers scale.
      </p>

      <h3>Cruise Line</h3>
      <p>
        Passenger cruise operator. Cruise line benefits. Guest service focus. Cruises offer variety.
      </p>

      <h3>Tanker Operations</h3>
      <p>
        Oil or chemical carrier. Energy company benefits. Specialized cargo. Tankers offer compensation.
      </p>

      <h3>Offshore</h3>
      <p>
        Platform supply or offshore support. Offshore benefits. Rotation schedules. Offshore offers intensity.
      </p>

      <h3>Yacht/Private</h3>
      <p>
        Private vessel command. Owner-provided benefits. Intimate crew. Private offers flexibility.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Ship Captains"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Ship Captains working abroad across maritime operations worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Maritime Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Master Mariner License</h3>
      <p>
        STCW certification. Flag state license. Tonnage endorsements. License authorizes command.
      </p>

      <h3>Medical Certificate</h3>
      <p>
        Maritime medical fitness. Regular renewal. Physical requirements. Medical enables service.
      </p>

      <h3>Sea Time</h3>
      <p>
        Documented experience. Progressive responsibility. Vessel types. Sea time builds qualification.
      </p>

      <h3>Specialized Endorsements</h3>
      <p>
        Tanker. Passenger. Ice navigation. Endorsements expand capability.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Isolation</h3>
      <p>
        Extended voyages. Limited contact. Command responsibility. Mental health support critical.
      </p>

      <h3>Medical Access</h3>
      <p>
        Remote locations. Limited facilities. Evacuation needs. Emergency coverage essential.
      </p>

      <h3>Sleep Patterns</h3>
      <p>
        Watch schedules. Port turnarounds. Time zone crossing. Wellness support valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Medical Certification</h3>
      <p>
        Fitness requirements. Regular examinations. Loss risk. Loss of license coverage important.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Navigation</h3>
      <p>
        Route planning. Weather assessment. Traffic management. Navigation ensures safety.
      </p>

      <h3>Crew Management</h3>
      <p>
        Personnel oversight. Team coordination. Conflict resolution. Crew management enables operations.
      </p>

      <h3>Safety</h3>
      <p>
        Emergency preparedness. Regulatory compliance. Risk assessment. Safety protects all.
      </p>

      <h3>Cargo/Passengers</h3>
      <p>
        Cargo operations. Passenger welfare. Loading oversight. Cargo responsibility core.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Steady Demand</h3>
      <p>
        Global trade dependent. Experience valued. Retirement attrition. Demand steady.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Fleet Captain. Marine Superintendent. Port Captain. Shore management. Multiple paths available.
      </p>

      <h3>Credential Portability</h3>
      <p>
        STCW recognized globally. Flag state specifics. Experience transfers. Core skills portable.
      </p>

      <h3>Field Evolution</h3>
      <p>
        Technology integration. Environmental compliance. Automation trends. Field evolving continuously.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a ship captain considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Shipping companies provide benefits. Flag state licensing matters. Extended voyages typical. Isolation significant.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do employers provide international coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Shipping companies typically yes. P&I coverage for work-related. Personal coverage important. Verify specifics.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is emergency evacuation coverage important?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Critical for mariners. Ocean locations remote. Medical facilities distant. Evacuation coverage essential.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do maritime credentials transfer internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            STCW provides baseline. Flag state endorsement needed. Experience recognized. Core skills portable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is loss of license insurance important?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Essential for captains. Medical conditions career-ending. Command dependent on fitness. Priority coverage.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Global trade continues. Experienced captains valued. Technology changing role. Outlook stable.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by evaluating shipping company benefits packages. Prioritize emergency evacuation coverage for remote operations. Ensure mental health support for command isolation. Consider loss of license coverage for career protection.
      </p>
      <p>
        Ship Captains command global commerce. Your coverage should support maritime command careers—addressing isolation and remote location challenges, covering health maintenance, and protecting you across maritime operations worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Maritime Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Ship Captains working abroad across maritime operations worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
